COMIS Reference table (which is used by the Drug Product Reference File to generate Approved Drug Products with Therapeutic Equivalence Evaluations (a.k.a. "The Orange Book")), and the Drug Registration and Listing Database, Office of Epidemiology and Biosurveillance Database.  Also, the names (but not the definitions or the numeric codes) that are represented in blue have been harmonized with the E2B route of administration terms for the International Conference on Harmonization (ICH).
